# Kavi ki Vidya Todo

Use this as the user-owned setup checklist. Tell Codex when an item is done; Codex will verify it and then tick it here.

## Backend Storage

- [x] Create a Supabase project for Kavi ki Vidya.
- [x] Add public Supabase URL and publishable key to the Expo env file.
- [x] Create the `learner_progress` table in Supabase using the schema in `docs/technical/backend.md`.
- [x] Add `SUPABASE_URL` to the local server env file.
- [x] Add `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to the local server env file.
- [x] Set `PROGRESS_STORAGE_PROVIDER=supabase-rest` when ready to test Supabase-backed progress sync.
- [x] Run a Supabase-backed progress sync test and confirm progress still appears on the Profile tab.

## Account And Persistence

- [x] Remove Google and Apple OAuth from the current production scope.
- [x] Use a local learner profile with Supabase-backed progress persistence.

## OpenAI And Voice

- [x] Confirm OpenAI API billing/credits are active for the API key.
- [x] Confirm `OPENAI_API_KEY` is present only in server-side env files, not in any `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` variable.
- [x] Test voice transcription from the iOS simulator/device microphone.
- [ ] Test one complete speaking session: record, transcribe, coach reply, feedback, and review item.

## Release Preparation

- [x] Decide whether the first backend target is Supabase or a custom managed API.
- [ ] Decide the first internal testing platform: TestFlight, Android internal testing, or both.
- [ ] Create production privacy copy for speech audio, AI processing, progress sync, and account deletion.
- [ ] Prepare app store metadata: app name, subtitle, screenshots, support URL, and privacy policy URL.
